{"id":14880757,"mediaExerciseId":"58735d85-1b22-4a77-abe5-1f84ff496643","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"2","chapterTitle":"Financial Statements, Taxes, and Cash Flow","groupId":612265,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":43,"solutions":[{"id":5900769,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are asked to determine the net capital spending for 2018 of Logano Driving School.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Net Capital Spending** is the amount of money that a company spends on purchasing new capital.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Net Capital Spending is computed as follows:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{NCS} &= \\text{Net Fixed Asset CY} - {\\text{Net Fixed Asset BY}} + {\\text{Depreciation}}\\\\[1pt]\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere:\n\nNCS - Net Capital Spending\nCY - Current Year\nBY - Base Year ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/2d4315cc7911730b44e59b2cd76f4bd1/2b31fd31adeacffbecfd5ac2bce3d671/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/2d4315cc7911730b44e59b2cd76f4bd1/2b31fd31adeacffbecfd5ac2bce3d671/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's determine the given amounts in the problem.\n\n\n|Particulars | Amounts ($)| \n|--|--:| \n|Net Fixed Asset 2017| 2.4 million| \n|Net Fixed Asset 2018| 3.3 million| \n|Depreciation |319,000 | \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/2d4315cc7911730b44e59b2cd76f4bd1/b86fac3fa01ed2eaf88026664b6727dd/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/2d4315cc7911730b44e59b2cd76f4bd1/b86fac3fa01ed2eaf88026664b6727dd/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's now compute for the net capital spending using the equation in step 3.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{NCS} &= \\text{Net Fixed Asset CY} - {\\text{Net Fixed Asset BY}} + {\\text{Depreciation}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{3,300,000} - {\\text{2,400,000}} + {\\text{319,000}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\boxed{\\textbf{\\$1,219,000}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nTherefore, the net capital spending of Logano Driving School is **$1,219,000**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":234,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/2d4315cc7911730b44e59b2cd76f4bd1/c07beef991b6a4983f6ad99ced2419d8/lateximg_large.png","width":1108},"regular":{"height":119,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/2d4315cc7911730b44e59b2cd76f4bd1/c07beef991b6a4983f6ad99ced2419d8/lateximg.png","width":556}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"0a50fa3d-3e1c-42a1-b081-6e2d8764670a","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["